		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=5121"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=5121')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=4583&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=The+simple%2C+most+logical+solution+to+focus+items%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> We all have seen that focus items now in place are somewhat screwed up.  50+ zones dropping tier 2 items, while mid 30s zone dropping tier 3?</P><P>Or how about the items that are basically very hard to get for a class when one component of that piece is for another chars epic?</P><P>My simple solution:</P><P>Questable focus items.  You go talk to some guy, and he tells you to get Extended Affliction, you need to go talk to some other guy, who tells you to bring back items, then talk to other guy, blah blah, etc etc.</P><P>Instead of you receiving an item, you CHOOSE which item you want the focus on.  You give that item to the final guy, and he returns it with the focus on it. That item then becomes No Drop.  This makes sense to me, as we can all have items we normally wear with focus effects on them.  It won't screw up the economy in anyway, and we won't be trying to take loot that we wouldnt normally use.  TADA!</P><P>Make the quest long and tedious because that is in VI's nature, but let choose which focus items we want to go on which item.</P><P>Any way, something along those lines.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=134799" target="_blank">Warlock of Terris-Thule</a><BR></font></td>

